10921 
10922 
10923 
10924 WCHAR ff_convert (  /* Converted code, 0 means conversion error */
10925     WCHAR   src,    /* Character code to be converted */
10926     UINT    dir     /* 0: Unicode to OEMCP, 1: OEMCP to Unicode */
10927 )
10928 {
10929     const WCHAR *p;
10930     WCHAR c;
10931     int i, n, li, hi;
10932 
10933 
10934     if (src < 0x80) {   /* ASCII */
10935         c = src;
10936     } else {
10937         if (dir) {      /* OEMCP to unicode */
10938             p = oem2uni;
10939             hi = sizeof(oem2uni) / 4 - 1;
10940         } else {        /* Unicode to OEMCP */
10941             p = uni2oem;
10942             hi = sizeof(uni2oem) / 4 - 1;
10943         }
10944         li = 0;
10945         for (n = 16; n; n--) {
10946             i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
10947             if (src == p[i * 2]) break;
10948             if (src > p[i * 2])
10949                 li = i;
10950             else
10951                 hi = i;
10952         }
10953         c = n ? p[i * 2 + 1] : 0;
10954     }
10955 
10956     return c;
10957 }

10961 WCHAR ff_wtoupper ( /* Upper converted character */
10962     WCHAR chr       /* Input character */
